modules.description: This module handles Htmx-specific interactions by inspecting incoming requests and modifying responses to control client-side behavior. It provides access to Htmx request metadata like triggers, targets, and prompts, and allows setting response headers to manipulate navigation, swapping, and event triggering. Concrete use cases include dynamically updating page sections based on user input, showing confirmation prompts before form submissions, and triggering client-side JavaScript events after content swaps.
